.TH _PRINTF 3 "November 24, 2025" "_printf Manual Pages" "Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
_printf \- custom implementation of the printf function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
_printf(const char *format, ...);

.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf
function produces output according to a format string.
It mimics the standard C library
.BR printf (3)
with support for a subset of format specifiers.

The
.I format
string is parsed character by character. Ordinary characters are written
to standard output. Conversion specifiers introduced by
.B %
are interpreted as follows:

.TP
.B %c
Print a single character.
.TP
.B %s
Print a string. If the string is NULL, "(null)" is printed.
.TP
.B %d, %i
Print a signed integer in decimal.
.TP
.B %b
Print an unsigned integer in binary.
.TP
.B %u
Print an unsigned integer in decimal.
.TP
.B %o
Print an unsigned integer in octal.
.TP
.B %x
Print an unsigned integer in hexadecimal (lowercase).
.TP
.B %X
Print an unsigned integer in hexadecimal (uppercase).
.TP
.B %%
Print a literal percent sign.
.TP
Any other character following
.B %
is printed verbatim, preceded by
.B % .

If
.I format
is NULL or an incomplete specifier is encountered, the function returns
.B -1
to indicate an error.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The function returns the number of characters printed, or
.B -1
if an error occurs.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
_printf("Hello %s!\\n", "world");
   prints: Hello world!

_printf("Binary: %b\\n", 5);
   prints: Binary: 101

_printf("Hex: %x, Octal: %o\\n", 255, 255);
   prints: Hex: ff, Octal: 377
.fi
.SH FILES
main.h
.br
_putchar.c
.br
_printf.c
.br
numbers.c
.SH SEE ALSO
printf(3)
